+## Code Review Report: staffordersmobile.jsx
+
+### Summary
+Scoped review was limited to Fix 1-3 only. The current file still contains all three requested issues: the old bill icon, the duplicate `Стол` prefix in the group header, and card-level CTA logic that still fails for ready/custom-stage orders.
+
+### Critical Issues (P0) — Must Fix
+None in this scoped review.
+
+### High Priority (P1) — Should Fix
+- [P1] Inline `OrderCard` CTA is still broken for ready/custom-stage orders. `staffordersmobile.jsx:1134` renders the button only when `statusConfig.nextStageId || statusConfig.nextStatus`, and `staffordersmobile.jsx:1039` makes the card action a no-op on the same condition. In stage mode, `getStatusConfig` returns the last configured stage with `nextStageId: null`, `nextStatus: null`, and no terminal marker (`staffordersmobile.jsx:3039`-`3056`), even though batch actions already special-case `config.isFinishStage` to `served` (`staffordersmobile.jsx:1521`-`1523`). This still blocks the intended inline `Выдать` action on ready/custom-stage orders. FIX: expose terminal/actionable state in `getStatusConfig`, derive card button visibility from that state instead of raw next-link IDs, and add the same `isFinishStage => served` fallback to `OrderCard.handleAction`.
+
+### Medium Priority (P2) — Recommended
+- [P2] Bill summary still uses `DollarSign` instead of `Receipt`. `staffordersmobile.jsx:1893` still renders `<DollarSign ... />`, so the waiter keeps seeing a dollar glyph before `Счёт`. FIX: replace only that one usage with `<Receipt className="w-4 h-4 text-slate-500 shrink-0" />`.
+
+### Low Priority (P3) — Nice to Have
+- [P3] Table card title still duplicates the `Стол` prefix. `staffordersmobile.jsx:1398` still does `` `Стол ${tableData.name}` ``, so names already stored as `Стол N` render as `Стол Стол N`. FIX: guard the prefix with `startsWith('Стол')` and keep pickup/delivery logic untouched.
+
+### Statistics
+- Total issues: 3 (P0: 0, P1: 1, P2: 1, P3: 1)
+- Files analyzed: 1 target + 2 local context files
+- Lines of code: ~4019
